Wait, the code for zero[i] is: 

for i in range(1, 30):

    for each edge:

        if (w &1) and (w >>i &1):

            union u and v in zero[i]

So, for each i from 1 to 29, the DSU zero[i] connects nodes via edges that have both the 0th bit (since w&1 is true) and the i-th bit set.
